- Alias allows you to set aliases for commands.
- Syntax updated in UG
- `alias show` will display all aliases
- You currently can write over aliases, but cannot delete (yet)

- Aliases can now take entire command phrases, as opposed to single
  command words.
- Improve GUI output for showing aliases
- Improve tests for Aliases (in StudyTrackerParser)
- No tests written yet for the enhanced Alias

In JsonUserPrefsStorageTest,
readUserPrefs_fileInOrder_successfullyRead() and
readUserPrefs_extraValuesInFile_extraValuesIgnored() were failing
intermittently.

On some runs, the expected UserPrefs() had an alias `pwd:list` (wrong),
while on other instances it was `ls:list` (correct).

This caused failing tests and builds.

The issue was caused by, a few commits ago, DEFAULT_PROGRAM_ALIASES in
UserPrefs was wrapped with an ArrayList<>() constructor to allow the
list to be modifiable. Thus, despite it being a final variable, it could
be modified.

So, our other unit tests were actually modifying this ArrayList! To
solve this, the ArrayList<>() constructor was shifted to the userAliases
field instead.

Lesson learned: unit tests might not be as separated as you think. Also,
Arrays.asList() creates structurally unmodifiable Lists!!

See: https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ErraticTestFailure.html

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement Addition and Removal of Amenities
commitResults.messageBody: Some tests are commented out, they would be resolved in future commits.
Added function to allow for addition and removal of tags, and cleaned up some tests.
Enhanced amenities such that the amenities shown for a study spot is in sync with it.
Updates the gui such that the count shows the current number of study spots listed over the total number of study spots.
Updates the gui such when the opacity of the amenity icons change according to whether the amenity is present in the study spot.
Refactored StudySpot's Email field to an OperatingHours field instead.

Improved OperatingHours by only accepting valid time intervals whereby
the start time is less than the end time. Also, "-" is used to specify
that OperatingHours of a study spot has not been defined yet.

Included the case whereby although the minutes of the opening hours are
larger than that of the closing hours, the time interval is still valid
as the hours of the closing hours are larger than that of the opening
hours.
Refactor the Ui component such that it follows StudyTracker now.

Included implementation and design consideration details for removing
tags or amenities in an Edit Command.
Included implementation of operating hours of a study spot.
